==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pneumatics
<hw>Pneu*mat"ics</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>pneumatique</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>That branch of science which treats of the
mechanical properties of air and other elastic fluids, as of their
weight, pressure, elasticity, etc. See <er>Mechanics</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Philos. & Theol.)</fld> <def>The scientific study
or knowledge of spiritual beings and their relations to God, angels, and
men.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pocket</ent>⟦br⟧
